From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?NixOS-Fairphone-FP5?= <noreply@example.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: qcm6490-fairphone-fp5: add ST21NFCD NFC
 node

Add the ST21NFCD NFC controller node on I2C9. Hardware details from
Fairphone 5 Android kernel source (vendor/fp5/yupik-idp-pm7250b.dtsi
and yupik-pinctrl.dtsi):

  - I2C bus: qupv3_se9 (i2c9), address 0x28
  - Reset GPIO: GPIO 38 (active low)
  - IRQ GPIO: GPIO 41 (edge rising)
  - Clock request GPIO: GPIO 39 (unused by mainline st-nci driver,
    chip uses external 27.12 MHz crystal)

Signed-off-by: NixOS-Fairphone-FP5 <noreply@example.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcm6490-fairphone-fp5.dts | 14 +++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcm6490-fairphone-fp5.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcm6490-fairphone-fp5.dts
index 1234567890..abcdef0123 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcm6490-fairphone-fp5.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcm6490-fairphone-fp5.dts
@@ -1006,7 +1006,19 @@
 &i2c9 {
 	status = "okay";
 
-	/* ST21NFC NFC @ 28 */
+	st21nfcd: nfc@28 {
+		compatible = "st,st21nfcd-i2c";
+		reg = <0x28>;
+
+		interrupt-parent = <&tlmm>;
+		interrupts = <41 IRQ_TYPE_EDGE_RISING>;
+
+		reset-gpios = <&tlmm 38 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>;
+
+		ese-present;
+		uicc-present;
+		status = "okay";
+	};
 	/* VL53L3 ToF @ 29 */
 };
 
